commit.message:
Fix compilation with -fno-common

Fix compilation with -fno-common, default in upcoming gcc-10
Also see https://bugs.gentoo.org/708686
Add English README and make documentation consistent
Use TLSv1.2 if available
Remove compiler warnings

Don't use removed SSLv3_client_method() function

New OpenSSL version provides universal TLS_client_method(). If it's
available, use it. If not, use TLSv1_client_method() available even in
OpenSSL 0.9.6. Gadu-Gadu server supports TLS v1.2 at the moment, so it
doesn't make much sens to support SSLv3.
Strip local full path from doxygen output

fix TLS connections

Signed-off-by: Rafał Malinowski <rafal.przemyslaw.malinowski@gmail.com>
Remove superfluous protobuf-c fixes
Update internal libprotobuf-c to 1.2.1
Fix style
Fix clang scan-build false positive
Check all GnuTLS functions results. It's not a serious TLS threat, but still bad things may happen if GnuTLS is misbehaving at user's host
Use gnutls/openssl provided rand. We don't need its security yet, since oauth module is still in manual tests. Fixes Coverity warnings
Clean up skipped.c
Make skipped.c an autogenerated source
Display skipped tests in make check
Fix tests build with OpenSSL
Fix use of uninitialized variable in case of RAM exhaustion
Remove $ tags, as we don't use them with Git
Fix a memory leak in case of RAM exhaustion
Simplify gg_session_handle_chat_info_update code a bit

Merge pull request #21 from canthar/patch-1

Fix invalid buffer reallocation (resulting in invalid memory write) on chat info update.

Update handlers.c

Fix out of memory write.
Fix tests build without pthreads
Prefer win32 resolver on Windows
Don't cancel win32 pthreads, mingw don't like it
Don't change #pragma pack setting for includes

Revert "Detach pthread's thread with force mode "

This reverts commit 258b5949b14303d2efe6bcb938e562a9bb0b98d0.
